<br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#FF9933>(7/2/01 1:47:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  50pp for a GG</span><hr size=1> Lybernia was being &quot;nice&quot; and only charging 50pp for a GG.<br>
<br>
I once wrote a post on GG pricing.  It is prolly 10-50 pages back in either &quot;newsroom&quot; or &quot;editorials and rants&quot;.<br>
<br>
I'd just like to ask:  How is demanding 50pp for a GG being nice?  A nice person would say &quot;no charge&quot;.  A nice person, out to make a little bit of cash would say &quot;I usually work for donations. 10-50pp is typical.  A donation that you feel just would be divine.&quot;<br>
<br>
A jerk is going to say:  It's 50pp or i'll leave your ass here.   A BIGGER jerk will charge, straight up, some amount over 50pp.  THERE IS NOTHING WRONG WITH BEING A JERK OR A BIGGER JERK.  IT WOULD BE A PRACTICE of HIPOCRACY IF I SAID THERE WAS.<br>
<br>
My point is this:  When a person is doing GGs for cash, the money is there to compensate them for their time.  If you're going through a zone, and someone wants a GG, but you don't want to give it to them, they can offer money to you to intice you to GG them.   For me, unless the person is a friend of mine, they better offer a very large amount of money.  (minimum of 500pp, but it rises exponentially with the degree of importance that I place upon my business at the time.)<br>
Lastly, if you're a gater, you're just chillin, have nothing better to do, and you don't mind gateing them anyway, why charge at all?  A one time shot of 50pp isn't going to give you much.  At 47, you're better off going and kiting a HG or 2, because you'll get some exp. <br>
<br>
Basically, it's not nice to charge 50pp for a gate, if you're just chillin.  If you're busy, however, you're nice if you consent to gate them at all, even if you demand a blue diamond, a jade mace, or $100 sent to you via check or money order.<br>
<br>
However, form Lybernia's post, I got the impression that she was hanging out in FV (I might be wrong, because this is an assumption), and would therefore, have not been nice to charge 50pp for the gate.<br>
<br>
Cristo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#292947><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ulyberniabelisama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lybernia Belisama</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.sherilyn.net/misc/sherry.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Knight<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif></span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#FF9933>(7/2/01 4:50:31 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/sherilyn70/lybernia4a.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: 50pp for a GG</span><hr size=1> Where did I ever mention what I was doing?  How could you possibly get a feel for what I was doing?   I don't have a reputation for gating people around all night for money, that's for sure.  I have never done the gating for pp circuit.  <br>
<br>
For your information I had just logged in, was getting ready to run to dreadlands to hunt and saw someone advertising that they were paying for a gate to Great Divide, they had to advertise it several times.  Normally I say &quot;whatever you feel is fair&quot; but because of the conversation I had with this person I named an amount.   <p><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/sherilyn70/lybernia.GIF><BR>
